      <article class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-blue-700 mb-4">Top 5 Strategies for Betting the NBA Playoffs</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-6">Published on July 6, 2025 • By <span class="font-semibold text-gray-700">YourCapper Team</span></p>

        <img src="https://source.unsplash.com/1200x600/?nba,basketball" alt="NBA Playoffs" class="rounded mb-6 w-full h-auto">

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          The NBA Playoffs are a unique betting environment where public interest peaks and odds tighten. To navigate these waters, here are our top five strategies:
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">1. Focus on Team Depth</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Injuries and tight rotations can expose weaknesses. Evaluate bench performance as key starters play longer minutes.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">2. Watch Line Movements</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          In the playoffs, sharp money can cause significant shifts in point spreads. Tracking movement can reveal which side pros prefer.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">3. Consider Unders in Game Sevens</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Historically, Game 7s trend under as nerves and fatigue result in lower scoring.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">4. Study Coaching Adjustments</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Series are all about chess matches between coaches. Watch for lineup changes and defensive schemes.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">5. Keep Emotions in Check</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          The playoffs are exciting, but don’t let fandom influence your bankroll management.
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-8">
          Using these strategies can give you an edge as the stakes rise. Remember: discipline and data win over hype and emotion.
        </p>

